---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Cookies Policy - OPTYP" 
  description="Cookies Policy for OPTYP explaining how cookies and similar technologies are used to enhance your experience and analyze site performance.">

  <section class="relative py-20 px-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-black via-gray-900 to-black text-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl font-body">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white">Cookies Policy</h1>
        <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-400 to-green-500 mx-auto mb-8 rounded-full shadow-sm"></div>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          This Cookies Policy explains how OPTYP uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience, analyze traffic, and personalize content.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
          Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none space-y-12 text-gray-300">

        <!-- What Are Cookies -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
          <div class="glass-box p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p>
              Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help remember user preferences, 
              improve performance, and enable certain features such as login persistence or analytics.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Types of Cookies -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Necessary for the operation of our website (e.g., navigation, security, and session management).</li>
            <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Help us analyze website traffic, load speed, and page interactions.</li>
            <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember user preferences and enhance user experience.</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Used to track website performance and visitor behavior via tools like Google Analytics.</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Help personalize ads and track engagement across platforms (used only with user consent).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- How We Use Cookies -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">3. How OPTYP Uses Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            We use cookies to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Provide a secure and reliable user experience.</li>
            <li>Understand visitor behavior and improve site functionality.</li>
            <li>Store your language and theme preferences.</li>
            <li>Measure and optimize marketing campaign performance.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-4 glass-box p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/40">
            <p class="text-green-300 font-semibold">
              We never store personal information such as passwords or financial details in cookies.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Managing Cookies -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">4. Managing or Disabling Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            You can manage, disable, or delete cookies at any time through your browser settings. However, disabling essential cookies 
            may affect website functionality and certain features may not operate as intended.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
            <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Preferences → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
            <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
            <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and Site Permissions</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Third-Party Cookies -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            Some cookies are set by third-party services integrated on our site, such as analytics or embedded social media tools. 
            These external services may collect data under their own policies.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-400 text-sm">
            We recommend reviewing third-party privacy and cookie policies for additional details.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Consent -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">6. Your Consent</h2>
          <p>
            By continuing to use our website, you consent to the use of cookies in accordance with this policy. 
            On your first visit, you will be prompted to accept, reject, or customize cookie preferences.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Updates -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">7. Policy Updates</h2>
          <p>
            OPTYP reserves the right to update this Cookies Policy to reflect technological or legal changes. 
            The latest version will always be available on this page.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-green-500 text-white p-8 rounded-xl text-center shadow-xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Need Help Managing Cookies?</h2>
          <p class="mb-6">For any questions about our use of cookies or data practices, please contact us directly.</p>
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@optyp.com" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">info@optyp.com</a></p>
          <p><strong>Contact Page:</strong> <a href="/contact/" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">Visit Our Contact Page</a></p>
        </section>

      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- JSON-LD Structured Data for SEO -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "Cookies Policy - OPTYP",
    "url": "https://optyp.github.io/cookies/",
    "description": "Detailed Cookies Policy explaining how OPTYP uses cookies and tracking technologies for performance, security, and analytics purposes.",
    "inLanguage": "en",
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "OPTYP",
      "url": "https://optyp.github.io",
      "logo": {
        "@type": "ImageObject",
        "url": "https://optyp.github.io/images/logo.svg"
      },
      "contactPoint": {
        "@type": "ContactPoint",
        "email": "info@optyp.com",
        "contactType": "Customer Support",
        "availableLanguage": ["English"]
      }
    }
  }
  </script>

  <style>
    .glass-box {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      border: 1px solid rgba(20,184,166,0.4);
      border-radius: 1rem;
      backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    }
    article a {
      color: #5eead4;
      transition: color 0.3s ease;
    }
    article a:hover {
      color: #86efac;
    }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      * {
        animation-duration: 0ms !important;
        transition-duration: 0ms !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
